  "response": "The Jeep Wrangler offers several trims with notable differences:\n\n1. Sport\n- Base model\n- Fewest features\n- Most affordable\n- Basic off-road capabilities\n\n2. Sport S\n- Slightly more features than Sport\n- Added comfort options\n- Power windows/locks\n- More standard equipment\n\n3. Sahara\n- More street-oriented\n- More comfort features\n- Better on-road performance\n- Less aggressive off-road setup\n- More luxury amenities\n\n4. Rubicon\n- Most off-road focused trim\n- Heavy-duty suspension\n- Locking differentials\n- Larger off-road tires\n- Enhanced ground clearance\n- Advanced 4x4 system\n- Most expensive trim\n- Best for serious off-roading\n\n5. 4xe (Hybrid)\n- Plug-in hybrid version\n- Improved fuel efficiency\n- Electric driving mode\n- Available on multiple trim levels\n\nKey differences include:\n- Price point\n- Off-road capabilities\n- Comfort/luxury features\n- Wheel/tire configurations\n- Standard/optional equipment\n\nThe choice depends on your intended use (off-roading vs. daily driving) and budget.",
